&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;http://robotics.usc.edu/~uscauv/blog/data/uploads/images/robosub_2013_booth_action.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 660px; height: 393px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The USC Autonomous Underwater Vehicle team is committed to the design, construction, and control of a fully functional autonomous underwater vehicle (AUV). Our undergraduate student design team was formed in 2003 and participates annually in the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.auvsifoundation.org/foundation/competitions/robosub/&quot;&gt;International Robosub Competition&lt;/a&gt; hosted by the Office of Naval Research (ONR) and the Association for Unmanned Vehicle Systems International (AUVSI). The competition challenges top universities from around the world to create and program autonomous underwater vehicles capable of completing a variable series of tasks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	USC AUV is a student-run organization with software, electrical, mechanical and administrative subteams. Together we work to develop cutting-edge hardware and software for our AUV while providing a unique and rewarding experience for every member. Want to meet our &lt;a href=&quot;http://robotics.usc.edu/~uscauv/blog/index.php?id=gallery&quot;&gt;members&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;
